solutionCode.javascript:
    ```javascript
function subsequenceORSum(nums) {
    let result = 0;
    for (let num of nums) {
        result |= num;
    }
    return result;
}
```

    For each integer in the array, we use the bitwise OR operation to accumulate the results, since it ensures that we don't lose any set bit while combining numbers. At the end, the result variable holds the bitwise OR sum of all subsequences in the array. This is an O(n) solution, as it iterates through the input array once.

solutionCode.java:
    ```java
public int subsequenceORSum(int[] nums) {
    int result = 0;
    for (int num : nums) {
        result |= num;
    }
    return result;
}
```

